  <brief_title>WelChol® and Sulfonylurea in Treating Patients With Type 2 Diabetes</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multi-Center, Randomized, Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled, Parallel-Group Study of the Efficacy and Safety of WelChol® in Type 2 Diabetics With Inadequate Glycemic Control on Sulfonylurea Monotherapy or Sulfonylurea Therapy in Combination With Other Oral Anti-Diabetic Agents</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Daiichi Sankyo, Inc.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Daiichi Sankyo, Inc.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to see how safe and effective and tolerable the use of
      colesevelam hydrochloride is for type 2 diabetes when added to sulfonylurea alone or in
      combination with other anti-diabetic drugs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
